The paper discusses error control for random linear network coding, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed decoder architectures also involve hardware implementation, which falls under the category of computer systems and embedded systems (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the computational complexities of the rank metric decoders, which is a topic related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the throughput achieved by the proposed decoder architectures, which is a topic related to computer communication networks (cs.CC).
